# cost.jsonl Schema
# .agents/sessions/templates/cost.jsonl.schema
# Source: agentic_system_design.md §10.2

Every line in .agents/cost.jsonl is a JSON object:

{
  "ts":                "ISO-8601 timestamp",
  "session_id":        "sess_<ulid>",
  "agent":             "agent role name",
  "task_id":           "task_<ulid>",
  "model":             "gemini-2.5-pro | claude-opus | gpt-4o",
  "input_tokens":      12500,
  "output_tokens":     3200,
  "cached_tokens":     4000,
  "tool_calls":        8,
  "tool_cache_hits":   3,
  "estimated_cost_usd": 0.0240
}

## Cost Estimation Formulas

### Token Cost (approximate — varies by model pricing):
- Uncached input: $2.50 / 1M tokens → ($0.0000025 per token)
- Cached input: $0.625 / 1M tokens → ($0.000000625 per token)
- Output: $10.00 / 1M tokens → ($0.00001 per token)

### Cache Efficiency:
- Cache hit rate = tool_cache_hits / tool_calls
- Target: > 40% cache hit rate for routine sessions

## Rules

- Append-only — one entry per agent activation (per task)
- session-level cost = SUM of all entries with matching session_id
- /retro reads this file to produce cost breakdown by agent and division
- /learn may read this file to identify expensive patterns worth caching
